          <avActivityHighlights>Wind slabs and wet snow represent the main danger.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>As a consequence of warming during the day individual small to medium-sized wet avalanches are possible above approximately 1300 m. &lt;br/&gt; In the vicinity of peaks a dangerous avalanche situation will be encountered in some localities. The more recent wind slabs are easy to recognise and can be released easily. &lt;br/&gt; Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground and reach medium size in some cases.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The solar radiation will give rise as the day progresses to rapid moistening of the snowpack. &lt;br/&gt;</snowpackStructureComment>
